<li style="padding: 2px;"><span>Botanical Garden and the jungle village, constructed during the colonial era by the English. It is the second in Africa after that of Kenya.</span></li>
<li style="padding: 2px;"><span>The Victoria Zoo. It is of re-creative aesthetic, scientific or cultural interest and regroups wild animal species, which constitute sufficient seduction to visitors. Amongst the mammals found there are: the mandrill (Pan Troglodytes). The reptile population is represented by African crocodiles and pythons.</span></li>
<li style="padding: 2px;"><span>The Fishermen’s Village</span></li>
